The Board may make an award only if the claimant, as a result of the injury on which the claim is based, has:
incurred at least $100 in unreimbursed and unreimbursable expenses or indebtedness reasonably incurred or claimed for:
medical care;
expenses for eyeglasses and other corrective lenses;
mental health counseling;
funeral expenses;
repairing, replacing, or cleaning property;
disability or dependent claim; or
other necessary services; or
lost at least 2 continuous weeks' earnings or support.
